{
  "stem": "26728.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, there were instruments of torture in every camp, then in-- some of these were in special places, some of these were-- that had been moved from their original location to where they could be seen by troops because Buchenwald was one of the camps that Eisenhower said, I want to troops to go through this camp.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So a lot of American soldiers went through the camp after we left.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of the most unusual things-- and I couldn't figure this out till someone explained it to me-- was what they called the swing.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And what it was, it was a, a, a round pole, probably made out of some very strong wood, probably this, this thick.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was built like a swing, you know, with-- like you could hook it to a swing, to a hook, and if it wasn't a round pole, if it had been flattened, it would be a little seat for a kid's swing.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But this pole was round, and the way it worked was-- and I never would have figured this out.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They, they tied the person's hands behind his back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they put this pole, which has chains on it, behind his knees, and they tie his knees-- his feet to his back.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In other words, his, his, his hands and his feet are behind his back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He's hanging upside down with this pole, which is the seat for this-- would have been the seat for the swing if it was a swing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's what they called it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and it's hooked onto a swivel, a chain, kind of like a tripod with a chain.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then they have-- and it-- and it swivels.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So you could spin the guy like this.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
